Bank of America Merrill Lynch Announces Appointments in Southern Africa

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-05-16T13:37:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/bank-of-america-merrill-lynch-announces-appointments-in-southern-africa.html
Bank of America Merrill Lynch
appointed Murray Stewart managing director of corporate broking
and equity capital markets in southern  Africa .  The company appointed Marius Strydom and Andrew Snowdowne
as directors of its southern African equity research team, the
company said in an e-mailed statement from London today.
Strydom, who will head South African financial-industry
research, joins the company from Renaissance BJM Securities,
while Snowdowne, who will lead mining and resources research,
was a director at UBS AG.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  